[5] Iowa (Kossuth County): back yard flock
Date: Mon 25 Apr 2022
Source: The Gazette [abridged, edited]
https://www.thegazette.com/agriculture/bird-flu-hits-backyard-flock-in-kossuth-county/


An outbreak of highly contagious bird flu has been discovered in a backyard flock in north-central Iowa's Kossuth County, state agriculture officials announced Monday [25 Apr 2022].

It brings to 18 the number of outbreaks confirmed so far this year [2022] in Iowa, all since the start of March [2022].

